# Telegram Bot Project Structure

## File Structure:
```
py-telegram/
├── bot.py              # Main entry point
├── config.py           # Configuration and environment variables
├── services/
│   ├── __init__.py     # Makes services a package
│   ├── bot_service.py  # Bot logic and operations
│   └── logger.py       # Logging functionality
├── handlers/
│   ├── __init__.py     # Makes handlers a package
│   ├── commands.py     # Command handlers (/start, /help, etc)
│   └── messages.py     # Message handlers
├── .env                # Environment variables (DO NOT COMMIT)
└── requirements.txt    # Python dependencies

```

## Installation:
```bash
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

## Setup:
1. Create .env file with:
   - TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN
   - GROQ_API_KEY
   - LOG_GROUP_ID (optional)

2. Run the bot:
   ```bash
   python3 bot.py
   ```

## Benefits of this structure:
- Easy to maintain and update
- Separated concerns (handlers, services, config)
- Easy to add new features
- Better testing capabilities
- Clean and organized code